extends ../../../layout

block splash

block content
  .container.documentation
    .row
      .col-md-12
        h1.page-header <small>conjure-up</small> // Documentation
    .row
      .col-xs-3.col-md-3.well
        include ../../_nav
      .col-xs-9.col-md-9
        h2 Usage
        p
          | <strong>conjure-up</strong> supports summoning spells from several remote repositories.
          | Below are some examples:

        h4.page-header Charmstore
        p
          | Deploy conjure-up enabled spells from jujucharms.com
          .well
            .install-code
              | $ conjure-up ~conjure/openstack-novalxd
          | This will pull the conjure-up enabled spell from https://jujucharms.com/u/conjure/openstack-novalxd
        h4.page-header GitHub
        p
          | Not quite ready to push your spell to the charm registry? That's ok, simply push your spell to GitHub and conjure-up can deploy from there:
          .well
            .install-code
              | $ conjure-up juju-solutions/bundle-observable-kubernetes
          | This would pull from GitHub repo https://github.com/juju-solutions/bundle-observable-kubernetes
        h4.page-header Remote Web Server
        p
          | <strong>conjure-up</strong> will also support downloading directly from a webserver. For example, if you have your spell zipped up and stored at http://example.com/my-conjure-spell.zip you could install it like so:
          .well
            .install-code
              | $ conjure-up http://example.com/my-conjure-spell.zip
